  "rawText": "English For Today 3\nB2. Match a word from Column A with a word (or words) from\nColumn B that has (or have) similar meaning.\nColumn A Column B\ninteresting lovingly\nfrightened amusing\nhappy afraid\nexcited glad\nwarmly thrilled\nB3. Talk about your first day at school and how you felt-happy, frightened,\nthrilled or shy. Work in groups.\nB4. Now, write a paragraph on how you felt on your first day at school\nand why you felt so.\nC. Read the following poem and complete this lesson with fun and\nlaughter.\nLet’s Play\n- Kate Greenaway\nSchool is over,\nOh, what fun!\nLessons finished,\nPlay begun.\nWho'll run fastest,\nYou or I?\nWho'll laugh loudest?\nLet us try.\nC1. Notice the use of punctuation marks in the poem. Why are the\nexclamation marks (!), the question marks (?), and the full stops (.)\nused in these places?",
